Gradefast has evaluated 3 themes from e-Yantra Robotics Competition and was tested with 2 themes from the last year. It was also used to assess practical exams of CS 296 (Software System Lab) at IIT Bombay. It was one of factors that we relied on to scale the competition by 4 times than in earlier years.

Sum of subsets problem, identifying digits, and finding shortest path in image of a maze.

First time use of gradefast took time because of the learning curve involved. But later, we could completely focus on writing test class hardly caring about other code. More modularity, maintainability. Logging feature made it possible to easily go through and verify the failing tests.
Without gradefast it would take 2.5 days, was done in half a day with it. Had to manually do some part of 10% of the submissions due to some issue with oct2py library. Reusing scripts was easy.

With gradefast taking care of entire pipeline, it's really easy to see the results right away. Another thing we liked about it are the utility methods it provides to save time. Sometimes the submissions come later than deadline, so we do evaluation in stages. Gradefast considers this scenario and provides aggregate methods and methods for storing.
